### What problem does this feature solve?
I'm using .vue components containing html and styles. I want to use a container wrapped into an iframe. I'm using the following code. 

    new Vue({
      el:iframeContainer,  // reference to a container element within an iframe
      template: '<Panel/>',
      components : { Panel }
    });

The rendered html gets injected properly, but the generated style tag does not. It gets injected into the default (main) document head element, which makes no sense in this case cause it's isolated from the rendered html.

One solution would be to have an option to configure custom document object. 
Another option would be to make sure that both (html and styles) get injected into the same isolated context (document).     

I would prefer the first one. 

### What does the proposed API look like?
Vue.options.document = myIframe.contentDocument.

Vue.document = Vue.options.document || document;

